{
	"info": {
		"name": "Zia Payment API",
		"description": "Complete collection for the Zia payment aggregator API — merchant endpoints, portal (frontend) endpoints, and PSP webhook ingestion.\n\n## Authentication\n\n- **Merchant API**: `Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}` — API key created via the portal (Create API Key).\n- **Portal API**: `Authorization: Bearer {{portal_token}}` — session token returned by `POST /api/v1/auth/login`.\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. **Signup** → creates a merchant workspace and user account. Run once.\n2. **Login** → saves `portal_token` for all subsequent portal requests.\n3. **Portal Auth required** → dashboard, transactions, payouts, customers, team, developer, notifications, profile.\n4. **Create API Key** → saves the raw key (shown only once; copy it).\n5. **Merchant API** → payment intents, checkout, merchant dashboard — use `{{api_key}}`.\n\n## Webhook Caveats\n\nWebhook endpoints return **200** for registered PSP connectors (mpesa, paystack) and **404** for unregistered ones (kcb, pesalink). Connectors register at startup only when their env vars (`KCB_CONSUMER_KEY`, `PESALINK_API_TOKEN`, etc.) are non-empty.\n\n## Base URL\n\nSet `base_url` to the running API instance (default `http://localhost:8080`).",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{ "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8080", "type": "string" },
		{ "key": "api_key", "value": "YOUR_MERCHANT_API_KEY", "type": "string" },
		{ "key": "portal_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
		{ "key": "payment_intent_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
		{ "key": "checkout_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
		{ "key": "customer_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
		{ "key": "invite_email", "value": "colleague@example.com", "type": "string" }
	],
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Health",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "GET /health",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test(\"status is ok\", () => {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
									"    pm.expect(pm.response.json().primaryData.status).to.eql(\"ok\");",
									"});"
								]
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": "{{base_url}}/health"
					}
				}
			]
		},
